Roydon has many old houses with weather-boarding fronts. Since the Second World War there has been a lot of building, and a small estate of expensive housing was being built when we visited the village. Roydon is one of those areas which is attractive to people with money who wish to get out of Harlow. Many of those people go to London every day to work.
{Little Parndon}
Most of the houses in Little Parndon have been built since the beginning of the new town. Parndon Hall has been preserved and is now used as the records office for Area Health. The site of Canons is now used as the Club House at Canons Brook Golf Course.
